{"pageProps":{"tutorial":{"title":"CSS Colors","slug":"css-colors","subject":"CSS","category":"Web Development","level":"Beginner","estimated_read_time":"15 mins","prerequisites":["CSS Syntax"],"learning_objectives":["Understand CSS Color names","Understand RGB and RGBA values","Understand HEX values","Understand HSL and HSLA values"],"theory":"Colors in CSS can be specified in various ways:\n\n1.  **Predefined Color Names**: e.g., `red`, `blue`, `tomato`.\n2.  **RGB**: `rgb(red, green, blue)`. Values range from 0 to 255.\n3.  **HEX**: `#RRGGBB`. Hexadecimal notation for Red, Green, and Blue (00 to FF).\n4.  **HSL**: `hsl(hue, saturation, lightness)`. More intuitive for changing shades.\n5.  **RGBA/HSLA**: Same as above but with an Alpha channel (opacity) from 0.0 to 1.0.","syntax":"/* Name */\ncolor: red;\n\n/* Hex */\ncolor: #ff0000;\n\n/* RGB */\ncolor: rgb(255, 0, 0);\n\n/* RGBA (50% transparent) */\ncolor: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5);","examples":[{"code":"<h1 style=\"background-color:Tomato;\">Tomato</h1>\n<h1 style=\"background-color:Orange;\">Orange</h1>\n<h1 style=\"background-color:DodgerBlue;\">DodgerBlue</h1>","output":"Three headings with distinct background colors.","explanation":"Using standard CSS color names."}],"common_mistakes":[{"mistake":"Forgetting the hash # in Hex codes","correction":"Hex codes must start with #.","example":"WRONG: color: ffffff;\nCORRECT: color: #ffffff;"}],"interview_questions":[{"question":"What is the difference between RGB and RGBA?","answer":"The 'A' stands for Alpha, which controls the opacity/transparency of the color. 0 is fully transparent, 1 is fully opaque.","difficulty":"Easy"},{"question":"What is the hex code for white and black?","answer":"White: #ffffff, Black: #000000.","difficulty":"Easy"}],"practice_problems":[{"problem":"Convert `rgb(0, 0, 0)` to HEX.","hint":"0 intensity for all channels.","solution":"#000000","difficulty":"Easy"}],"real_world_use_cases":[{"scenario":"Theme Transparency","description":"Using RGBA for overlay backgrounds (modals, tooltips) to show content underneath.","code":".overlay { background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5); }"}],"exam_notes":["There are 140 standard color names.","Hex codes are base-16.","Saturation in HSL is a percentage value."],"summary":"Colors bring life to web pages. Developers usually rely on Hex or RGB/RGBA for precise control over the design.","order":5},"courseTutorials":[{"slug":"css-introduction","path":"content/css/css-introduction.json","title":"Introduction to CSS","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":1},{"slug":"css-syntax","path":"content/css/css-syntax.json","title":"CSS Syntax","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":2},{"slug":"css-best-practices","path":"content/css/css-best-practices.json","title":"CSS Best Practices","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":3},{"slug":"css-borders","path":"content/css/css-borders.json","title":"CSS Borders","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":4},{"slug":"css-colors","path":"content/css/css-colors.json","title":"CSS Colors","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":5},{"slug":"css-backgrounds","path":"content/css/css-backgrounds.json","title":"CSS Backgrounds","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":6},{"slug":"css-comments","path":"content/css/css-comments.json","title":"CSS Comments","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":7},{"slug":"css-interview","path":"content/css/css-interview.json","title":"CSS Interview Preparation","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":8},{"slug":"css-margins","path":"content/css/css-margins.json","title":"CSS Margins","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":9},{"slug":"css-opacity","path":"content/css/css-opacity.json","title":"CSS Opacity","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS",